    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="659"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d659">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11663a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to President
                            <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I send despatch just received from the Secretary of the Navy: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Mayo reports, April 9, 5 p.m.:</p>
                        <p>“This forenoon Mexican soldiers arrested paymaster and whaleboat’s crew
                            of <hi rend="italic">Dolphin</hi>, part of whom were in boat with flag
                            flying, marched them two blocks through streets, then back to boat, and
                            there released them. General Zaragoza expressed regret verbally.</p>
                        <p>“In view of publicity of event, I have called for formal disavowal and
                            apology, punishment of officer in charge Mexican squad, and salute to
                            American flag within 24 hours from 6 p.m., Thursday.</p>
                        <p rend="right">“Mayo.”</p>
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I do not see that Mayo could have done otherwise. I await instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
